=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Env_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 470 Hz, featuring punchy attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is front_heavy, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: front_heavy

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 470.2192
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.5490
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5038
  pitch_clarity: 32.5112
  inharmonicity: 0.0056
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.4338
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Env Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Env.html
// Tags: Env, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
// an envelope in a synth
(
{
    var env = Env([0, 1, 0.5, 1, 0], [0.01, 0.5, 0.02, 0.5]);
    SinOsc.ar(470) * EnvGen.kr(env, doneAction: Done.freeSelf)
}.play
)
// an envelope to control a parameter in a pattern
(
Pbind(
    \note, Env([0, 12, 6, 13, 0], [1, 5, 2, 10]),
    \dur, 0.1
).play
)
